description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the position of Research Nurse to play a key role in a CRUK programme (UK Early Detection Initiative/UKEDI) aimed at detecting pancreatic cancer in individuals with new-onset diabetes mellitus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a motivated and enthusiastic individual with good communication and interpersonal skills to provide clinical research support. You will be an important member of the extended UKEDI team, which includes the chief investigator (CI), the clinical lead, the study coordinator, data manager, data officer, research technician, clinical research fellow, PhD student, and postdoctoral fellow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is based at The Royal Liverpool University Hospital, and will also involve liaising with local GPs and health centres to facilitate research clinics. Some local travel will be necessary, and a driving licence would be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for the day-to-day recruitment and follow-up of individuals recruited to the clinical study and you will work closely with the data officer, Chief Investigator and the wider project team to ensure successful completion of the study.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity, working with a world renowned research team at The University of Liverpool leading research in Pancreatic Cancer.&lt;/p&gt;
